snippet: Russia and the West are maneuvering ahead of a seemingly inevitable clash over Ukraine’s plan to hold a vote on May 25. Moscow would like the voting to be delayed.
abstract: Russia and the West are maneuvering ahead of a seemingly inevitable clash over Ukraine’s plan to hold a presidential election that Western powers view as crucial to restoring stability and that the Kremlin says will be illegitimate and should be delayed, particularly if government in Kiev cannot first stabilize the country.

byline.contributor: C. J. Chivers contributed reporting from Slovyansk, Ukraine; Alan Cowell from London; and David E. Sanger from Washington.

lead_paragraph: Russia and the West are maneuvering ahead of a seemingly inevitable clash over Ukraine’s plan to hold a vote on May 25. Moscow would like the voting to be delayed.

headline.main: As Ukrainian Election Looms, Western Powers and Russia Campaign for Influence
headline.print_headline: As Ukrainian Election Looms, Western Powers and Russia Campaign for Influence
